elative error of 23{\%}. Applying the CPTSM model to the Sea-viewing Wide Field-of-view Sensor (SeaWiFS) data and analyzing the errors from a match-up dataset of SeaWiFS and in situ data, we found that the average relative error was 24.5{\%}. We propose to use the CPTSM model to map TSM concentrations from satellite data in the ECS. {\textcopyright} 2012 Elsevier Inc.},
