ely among Omernik level III ecoregions in nutrient ecoregion II. Our analysis and the literature strongly suggest that 14 national nutrient ecoregions are too coarse to account for natural variation in stream nutrient concentrations. Setting appropriate national nutrient criteria will require finer-scale typology or classification of sites that better controls for natural variation.},
